== First round ==
Teams were drawn into nine groups of six teams to play home-and-away [[Round-robin tournament|round robin matches]] from November 2023 to October 2025. The winners of each group qualified directly to the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]], and the four best group runners-up advanced to a play-off to determine which team would advance to the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification#Inter-confederation play-offs|inter-confederation play-offs]].

=== Draw ===
The draw was held on 13 July 2023 at 15:00 [[Time in Ivory Coast|GMT]] ([[UTC±00:00|UTC±0]]) in [[Abidjan]], Ivory Coast.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://panafricafootball.com/learn-all-about-2026-fifa-world-cup-qualifying-in-the-caf-region-and-the-seeds/ |title=Learn all about 2026 FIFA World Cup qualifying in the CAF region and the seeds |first=Andrew |last=Olsson |website=Pan-Africa Football |date=4 July 2023 |access-date=6 July 2023 |archive-date=1 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231001141031/https://panafricafootball.com/learn-all-about-2026-fifa-world-cup-qualifying-in-the-caf-region-and-the-seeds/ |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name="draw">{{cite web |date=11 July 2023 |title=FIFA World Cup 2026 African Qualifiers Official Draw on 13 July |url=https://www.cafonline.com/press-release/news/fifa-world-cup-2026tm-african-qualifiers-official-draw-on-13-july |access-date=11 July 2023 |website=cafonline |publisher=[[Confederation of African Football|CAF]]}}</ref> All 54 FIFA-affiliated football associations from CAF entered qualification. However, Eritrea withdrew after the draw.<ref name="ERI withdrawal" /><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cafonline.com/news/statement-on-fifa-world-cup-2026-preliminary-competition/ |title=Statement on FIFA World Cup 2026 preliminary competition |publisher=CAF | accessdate=11 November 2023 |date=10 November 2023}}</ref>

The draw pots were announced on 30 June (numbers in parentheses indicate [[FIFA Men's World Ranking]] at the time of the draw):<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://dailypost.ng/2023/06/30/fifa-puts-super-eagles-in-pot-1-as-race-to-2026-world-cup-begins/ |location=Lagos, Nigeria|title=FIFA puts Super Eagles in Pot 1 as race to 2026 World Cup begins |newspaper=[[Daily Post (Nigeria)|Daily Post]]|first=Ifreke |last=Inyang |date=30 June 2023 |access-date=30 June 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cafonline.com/news-center/news/fifa-world-cup-2026-african-preliminary-qualifiers-draw-officially-conducted |title=FIFA World Cup 2026: African preliminary qualifiers draw officially conducted |publisher=CAF |date=13 July 2023 |access-date=13 July 2023}}</ref>

